race.comment: VIRESHA (12) got a long way back last start when favourite at Northam, rattling home to miss by 1.5L after being awkwardly away. She showed good ability there at just her second start and while she's likely to get back in the run again, she rates highly on the back of that effort. Can get the job done this time. ROCK THE MARKET (6) was very good on debut, with that form working out well as she went to the paddock. She trialled well recently behind Cannykev and we'll get a good read on that form in the race prior. Needs some luck from the gate but has shown enough to suggest she can win a race like this. BARRAQUITO (13) is on debut for Team Williams and Pike remains in the irons following his latest trial. The inside draw gives Pike options and they've taken a patient approach with her. Can repay their patience on debut. GODLESS STORM (3) wasn't far away last start and has to be included on that effort. RISING FAME (5) is not out of this with form tying through VIRESHA.
